 "transcript": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 2.48,
   "text": "What an American thinks about Nicaragua."
  },
  {
   "start": 6.78,
   "end": 10.82,
   "text": "Nicaragua is a country in Central America"
  },
  {
   "start": 10.82,
   "end": 14.94,
   "text": "Between just south of Honduras"
  },
  {
   "start": 14.94,
   "end": 19.57,
   "text": "And just north of Panama, I think."
  },
  {
   "start": 21.27,
   "end": 24.11,
   "text": "That country is pretty."
  },
  {
   "start": 24.23,
   "end": 28.07,
   "text": "They have this really big volcano"
  },
  {
   "start": 28.07,
   "end": 29.71,
   "text": "That's totally barren that I went by."
  },
  {
   "start": 29.71,
   "end": 32.39,
   "text": "And then they've got this really big lake"
  },
  {
   "start": 32.39,
   "end": 33.23,
   "text": "Called Lake Managua."
  },
  {
   "start": 33.97,
   "end": 37.15,
   "text": "And the town, the town of Managua,"
  },
  {
   "start": 37.37,
   "end": 38.75,
   "text": "Is right on the southern edge of it."
  },
  {
   "start": 38.93,
   "end": 40.51,
   "text": "And as you look in the lake,"
  },
  {
   "start": 40.55,
   "end": 41.51,
   "text": "You can't see the other side."
  },
  {
   "start": 41.59,
   "end": 44.23,
   "text": "So it's kind of like next to the ocean, you know."
  },
  {
   "start": 47.41,
   "end": 49.51,
   "text": "And they do have the ocean really close to the other side."
  },
  {
   "start": 50.89,
   "end": 54.05,
   "text": "But that downtown area,"
  },
  {
   "start": 54.43,
   "end": 55.49,
   "text": "That town was interesting"
  },
  {
   "start": 55.49,
   "end": 57.15,
   "text": "Because it had a really big earthquake"
  },
  {
   "start": 57.15,
   "end": 59.31,
   "text": "Back in like 1980."
  },
  {
   "start": 59.31,
   "end": 62.57,
   "text": "And they had this dictatorship"
  },
  {
   "start": 62.57,
   "end": 63.83,
   "text": "Controlling them."
  },
  {
   "start": 64.01,
   "end": 65.49,
   "text": "And they embezzled."
  },
  {
   "start": 65.67,
   "end": 67.43,
   "text": "They were given all this money to fix it up"
  },
  {
   "start": 67.43,
   "end": 68.51,
   "text": "From like the world,"
  },
  {
   "start": 68.79,
   "end": 72.99,
   "text": "From the IMF,"
  },
  {
   "start": 73.05,
   "end": 74.19,
   "text": "I don't know, World Health Organization,"
  },
  {
   "start": 74.29,
   "end": 75.37,
   "text": "All the other countries to get money."
  },
  {
   "start": 75.77,
   "end": 78.35,
   "text": "But the ruling family just embezzled the money"
  },
  {
   "start": 78.35,
   "end": 79.61,
   "text": "And they never fixed it up."
  },
  {
   "start": 79.61,
   "end": 84.69,
   "text": "So right there in downtown Managua,"
  },
  {
   "start": 84.83,
   "end": 87.89,
   "text": "Right next to the lake shore,"
  },
  {
   "start": 90.66,
   "end": 94.32,
   "text": "You can see the original courthouse building."
  },
  {
   "start": 94.82,
   "end": 96.06,
   "text": "It's just in ruins."
  },
  {
   "start": 96.28,
   "end": 97.88,
   "text": "It's just like crumbled and abandoned."
  },
  {
   "start": 98.76,
   "end": 100.18,
   "text": "And there's lots of buildings like that."
  },
  {
   "start": 100.18,
   "end": 103.5,
   "text": "Like all the five central downtown areas"
  },
  {
   "start": 103.5,
   "end": 104.24,
   "text": "Totally abandoned."
  },
  {
   "start": 105.72,
   "end": 107.88,
   "text": "And then the rest of the city"
  },
  {
   "start": 107.88,
   "end": 110.14,
   "text": "That's thriving and people are guzzing"
  },
  {
   "start": 110.14,
   "end": 111.72,
   "text": "Is just around that."
  },
  {
   "start": 113.36,
   "end": 114.94,
   "text": "Really weird sight, man."
  },
  {
   "start": 118.24,
   "end": 118.76,
   "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
   "start": 119.62,
   "end": 121.08,
   "text": "I don't remember interacting"
  },
  {
   "start": 121.08,
   "end": 122.32,
   "text": "With any of the people there though."
  },
  {
   "start": 122.5,
   "end": 123.88,
   "text": "They're not really that outgoing."
  },
  {
   "start": 124.96,
   "end": 126.88,
   "text": "A lot of people in Central America"
  },
  {
   "start": 126.88,
   "end": 128.22,
   "text": "Are not really that outgoing."
  },
  {
   "start": 128.44,
   "end": 130.44,
   "text": "They're not really that cheerful."
  },
  {
   "start": 131.06,
   "end": 132.44,
   "text": "Especially the Hondurans."
  },
  {
   "start": 134.02,
   "end": 137.02,
   "text": "But yeah,"
  },
  {
   "start": 137.08,
   "end": 138.0,
   "text": "And then I rode over to"
  },
  {
   "start": 138.0,
   "end": 141.44,
   "text": "The other lake,"
  },
  {
   "start": 141.52,
   "end": 142.32,
   "text": "Lake Nicaragua."
  },
  {
   "start": 142.86,
   "end": 146.7,
   "text": "And there's this town there"
  },
  {
   "start": 146.7,
   "end": 148.76,
   "text": "That looked like kind of an expat town."
  },
  {
   "start": 148.88,
   "end": 149.76,
   "text": "There are some expats"
  },
  {
   "start": 149.76,
   "end": 150.94,
   "text": "That look like they look there."
  },
  {
   "start": 153.04,
   "end": 160.03,
   "text": "And then they have this island"
  },
  {
   "start": 160.03,
   "end": 160.79,
   "text": "In the middle of it"
  },
  {
   "start": 160.79,
   "end": 165.91,
   "text": "That has two,"
  },
  {
   "start": 165.95,
   "end": 167.55,
   "text": "It's two volcanoes next to each other."
  },
  {
   "start": 167.55,
   "end": 170.95,
   "text": "And they were conjoined"
  },
  {
   "start": 170.95,
   "end": 172.65,
   "text": "Back like 300 years ago"
  },
  {
   "start": 172.65,
   "end": 173.93,
   "text": "When one of them erupted."
  },
  {
   "start": 175.51,
   "end": 176.23,
   "text": "But that island,"
  },
  {
   "start": 176.99,
   "end": 178.47,
   "text": "The main town of that island,"
  },
  {
   "start": 181.28,
   "end": 183.12,
   "text": "It had their central plaza"
  },
  {
   "start": 183.12,
   "end": 185.14,
   "text": "In the stores and stuff around it."
  },
  {
   "start": 185.38,
   "end": 187.36,
   "text": "But it was really basic."
  },
  {
   "start": 187.62,
   "end": 188.9,
   "text": "All the roads were dirt."
  },
  {
   "start": 190.38,
   "end": 191.72,
   "text": "And the road from the,"
  },
  {
   "start": 191.84,
   "end": 192.8,
   "text": "Where you get off the boat"
  },
  {
   "start": 192.8,
   "end": 193.86,
   "text": "To get to the town,"
  },
  {
   "start": 193.96,
   "end": 196.3,
   "text": "It's like a dirt road."
  },
  {
   "start": 196.64,
   "end": 197.94,
   "text": "Like a two-track dirt road."
  },
  {
   "start": 197.94,
   "end": 200.52,
   "text": "And yeah,"
  },
  {
   "start": 200.64,
   "end": 201.68,
   "text": "Like living on that island"
  },
  {
   "start": 201.68,
   "end": 202.48,
   "text": "Must be bizarre."
  },
  {
   "start": 202.72,
   "end": 211.83,
   "text": "Just totally basic."
  },
  {
   "start": 213.13,
   "end": 214.15,
   "text": "Just a couple of stores."
  },
  {
   "start": 214.75,
   "end": 217.12,
   "text": "I climbed the mountain,"
  },
  {
   "start": 217.22,
   "end": 217.82,
   "text": "But it was really,"
  },
  {
   "start": 217.96,
   "end": 218.6,
   "text": "Really foggy."
  },
  {
   "start": 221.54,
   "end": 221.9,
   "text": "And then,"
  },
  {
   "start": 222.0,
   "end": 222.54,
   "text": "Yeah,"
  },
  {
   "start": 222.68,
   "end": 223.86,
   "text": "But then you take the boat,"
  },
  {
   "start": 224.26,
   "end": 224.4,
   "text": "The,"
  },
  {
   "start": 225.12,
   "end": 227.3,
   "text": "To get into Costa Rica"
  },
  {
   "start": 227.3,
   "end": 228.1,
   "text": "On the southern end,"
  },
  {
   "start": 228.14,
   "end": 229.12,
   "text": "You take a boat ride."
  },
  {
   "start": 229.12,
   "end": 230.7,
   "text": "It's like a jungle safari."
  },
  {
   "start": 232.69,
   "end": 233.87,
   "text": "And you can see all these,"
  },
  {
   "start": 233.93,
